Class Star

  • java.lang.Object
    • Star
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ODESystem

    public class Star
extends java.lang.Object
implements ODESystem
    A class to store information regarding a firework star.

    The initial mass, the burn rate, the density, the current mass, the radius, the initial x and y velocities, the actual x velocity, the velocity magnitude, and the drag force are recorded.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    zackh_000

        A constructor for the Star class.
        Parameters:
        initialVX - The initial x velocity, not accounting for wind.
        initialVXA - The initial actual x velocity, accounting for wind.
        initialVY - The initial y velocity.
        airDensity - The air density in the environment surrounding the Star.
        dragCoeff - The drag coefficient for the star in its environment.
